comments: Mann (LAC) firms up in his screening position in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Brunson (DAL) maintains a rested forearm on Mann's (LAC) back and marginal contact occurs as Mann jumps toward the ball during rebounding.
Mann (LAC) and Bullock (DAL) engage and disengage with one another as the pick is set.
Porzingis (DAL) grasps and then quickly releases Coffey's (LAC) left arm as the pass into the post is made.
Coffey (LAC) is bringing his arm into a vertical position when he brushes Porzingis' (DAL) left arm during his upward shooting motion. The contact is marginal.
Bullock (DAL) moves into George's (LAC) path but the contact is marginal and George is able to move through it to the basket.
George (LAC) and Porzingis (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Brunson (DAL) does not bring any part of his hand underneath the ball as he dribbles inside the perimeter.
Winslow (LAC) brushes Brunson's (DAL) left arm and marginal contact occurs as Brunson dribbles ahead inside the perimeter.
Finney-Smith (DAL) and George (LAC) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Kennard (LAC) engages and disengages with Bullock (DAL) as Bullock moves to set the pick.
Kennard (LAC) brushes Brunson's (DAL) left arm as he hedges the pick and marginal contact occurs.
Mann (LAC) is collapsing his left forearm to his front as marginal contact occurs with Brunson's (DAL) right arm at the end of the drive.

Replay review of the foul called on Mann (LAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Brunson (DAL) leads with his right arm and initiates contact with Mann's head/neck area as he elevates for the shot attempt.
Bullock (DAL) lifts his right knee toward Jackson (LAC) and marginal contact occurs as Jackson dribbles across half-court.
Finney-Smith (DAL) and George (LAC) engage and disengage with one another as they move over the screen.
Jackson (LAC) mishandles the pass as he receives the ball, gathers it, and legally starts his dribble on the wing.
George (LAC) and Finney-Smith (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Finney-Smith (DAL) establishes verticality and is retreating away from Jackson (LAC) when marginal contact occurs with Jackson's side during the driving shot attempt.
Jackson (LAC) briefly has his arm around Porzingis' (DAL) midsection before quickly removing it during the inbound.
Kleber (DAL) and Mann (LAC) engage and disengage with one another as Kleber sets the pick and the defensive switch takes place.
Jackson (LAC) keeps his hand on the side of the ball as he turns to dribble up the sideline.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) moves forward into Jackson (LAC) and initiates body contact that affects Jackson's SQBR as he is passing.
Coffey (LAC) legally contests Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) jump shot attempt and any marginal contact that occurs is the result of Hardaway Jr. extending his right leg to the side.
Jackson (LAC) and Kleber (DAL) engage and disengage with one another following the release of the shot attempt.
